body:
@tgamblin said:
 > Currently, folks... have a lot of **bash** scripts built around Spack that are very complicated. 

IMHO, serious scripting with Spack should be done in Python, not Bash.  I think we might benefit from exporting a Spack API that people can write Python scripts to.  I think I've already done it a bit here and there; but making it standardized and available to the public; and pushing its use; might be beneficial.
